name: GUCCI
about: Gucci is a renowned Italian luxury fashion brand, famous for its timeless designs and high-quality products. Established in Florence in 1921, Gucci has become a symbol of elegance and sophistication. From iconic handbags to extraordinary runway shows, Gucci continues to redefine the world of luxury fashion and captivate audiences worldwide.

name: LOUIS VUITTON
about: Louis Vuitton is a French luxury fashion house known for its exquisite leather goods, ready-to-wear collections, and innovative accessories. Founded in 1854, Louis Vuitton has become synonymous with craftsmanship and elegance. From the iconic monogram pattern to cutting-edge collaborations, Louis Vuitton continues to push the boundaries of fashion and set new trends worldwide.

name: CHANEL
about: Chanel is a legendary French luxury fashion brand known for its iconic designs and innovative creations. Founded by Coco Chanel in 1910, the brand has revolutionized the world of fashion with its modern and elegant designs. From the iconic little black dress to the No. 5 perfume, Chanel has become a symbol of sophistication and timeless elegance, inspiring fashion enthusiasts worldwide.

name: DIOR

From stunning gowns to iconic fragrances, Dior continues to be at the forefront of the fashion industry, setting trends and captivating audiences around the globe.

name: RAG & BONE

Founded in 2002 by Marcus Wainwright and David Neville, the brand offers a mix of classic tailoring, utilitarian elements, and modern aesthetics. From its well-crafted denim pieces to its refined outerwear, Rag & Bone combines British heritage with a downtown New York sensibility.
